## Tools

* `equity_fundamental_income(symbol="{{ ticker }}", period="annual", limit=5)` — revenue.
* `equity_fundamental_balance(symbol="{{ ticker }}", period="annual", limit=5)` — cash_and_equivalents, total_debt, shareholders_equity, current_assets, current_liabilities.
* `equity_fundamental_cash(symbol="{{ ticker }}", period="annual", limit=5)` — free_cash_flow, capital_expenditure.
* `equity_historical_market_cap(symbol="{{ ticker }}"{% if as_of_date %}, start_date="{{ as_of_date }}", end_date="{{ as_of_date }}"{% endif %})` — market_cap.

## Rules

* All series **oldest -> newest**.
* `capital_expenditure_series`: POSITIVE absolute values.
* `null` for missing values.

* **Use the `execute_python` tool for any arithmetic** — ratio / margin derivations (e.g. `gross_margin = gross_profit / revenue`), per-share figures, `abs()` / sign handling, and series reversal or re-ordering. Call the tool and read the printed result; do NOT compute in your head.

